event_title: EVENT CANCELLED: Etape du Tour - 177k
event_desc: Temporary lazy copy-pasta:

event_attendees.name: Maciej Z
event_attendees.bio: Lazy cyclist

event_comments.event_comment:
OK, the countdown has begun until you must decide whether you will do the Etape du Tour in Nice on Sept. 6, 2020. The deadline is by July 21 you must inform ASO/TimeTo that you will NOT be attending. I almost missed the email from ASO/TimeTo, so I'm posting here to alert you to check your spam folders if you didn't see an email. Here is an FAQ related to the rescheduling: https://www.timeto.com/en-GB/sports/cycling/letape-du-tour-2020/mesures-covid-19/faq. 
So, just to help everyone in PCB who signed up (that's 20 of us, I believe), please be sure to not only decide by July 21 but to also - especially if you are planning to ride - please answer the survey I shared earlier (https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/LX9B6QP). That will help those who are planning to ride perhaps coordinate their travel and accommodations plans. So far, Luri is confirmed to go and I and likely to go as well.

You need a cover according to the Oui website: "Only folded or dismantled bikes, placed in a cycle bag (max 120x90 cm) can be transported in Thalys trains. You do not need to pay any extra fees." https://en.oui.sncf/en/train-services/bicycle-on-board#:~:text=TAKING%20YOUR%20BIKE%20IN%20FRENCH,are%20available%20for%20unfolded%20bicycles.
Thank you Maciej, Doug and Thierry for your responses to the survey. Is there anyone who is actually planning to ride on the rescheduled date Sept. 6?
